## Building Whack-a-Mole in Vue 3

**Mental model:** Two timers: a *spawn* interval that relocates the mole, and a *countdown* that ends the round. State is the active hole, score, time left, and playing flag. Whacking the active hole scores. Clear both intervals on stop and unmount.

### Step 1 — Game state
```js
const active = ref(-1);
const score = ref(0);
const time = ref(20);
const playing = ref(false);
```

### Step 2 — Start: launch both intervals
```js
function start() {
  score.value = 0; time.value = 20; playing.value = true;
  spawnId = setInterval(() => { active.value = Math.floor(Math.random() * HOLES); }, 700);
  tickId = setInterval(tick, 1000);
}
```

### Step 3 — Countdown that stops the game
```js
function tick() {
  time.value--;
  if (time.value <= 0) stop();
}
function stop() { playing.value = false; active.value = -1; clearInterval(spawnId); clearInterval(tickId); }
```

### Step 4 — Whack handler + cleanup
```js
function whack(i) { if (playing.value && i === active.value) { score.value++; active.value = -1; } }
onUnmounted(stop);
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Click empty hole | Only active hole scores. |
| Timer leak | `stop()` clears both; called in `onUnmounted`. |
| Restart | Reset score/time before relaunching. |

**Interview tip:** Keep the two intervals as separate handles you clear together in a single `stop()` (also wired to `onUnmounted`) — that centralization is what prevents orphaned timers.

